<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="522fe2d2-3b26-5a4b-9d99-48ad7360e620" activityNameId="e6c7ab94-e594-5c86-ac80-6f9292edb7b6" parentActivityId="c0e9c274-73ad-58e3-8d19-8ea18fb68897" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">glass wool mat production, with phenolic binder, uncoated, Saint-Gobain ISOVER SA</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">Gate-to-gate inventory: the dataset starts at the factory gate with raw material aquisition and covers the whole prodcution process from mixing of raw materials,  melting, fibre forming &amp; collecting, hardening &amp; curing and internal processes (preparation of binders, workshop, etc.). Further on, transportation of raw materials and energy carrier for furnace and infrastructure are included. The dataset does not contain packaging.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">Gate-to-gate inventory: the included activity ends before packaging the product, ready to be shipped. Treatment of waste flows from production are included via the respective datasets.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset is provided by Saint-Gobain ISOVER SA, CH-1522 Lucens and represents a cradle-to-gate inventory of the average production of all glass woll mats, produced with phenol-based binder in 2018 per kg. The average density of an St. Gobain ISOVER SA glass wool mat is 25.00 kg/m3.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">The following packaging per m3 is not included: corrugated board, mixed fibre, single wall: 7.44E-04 kg/m3; paper, wood containing, LWC: 2.39E-04 kg/m3: packaging film, LDPE: 2.25E-02 kg/m3; EUR-flat pallet: 4.17E-03 pce/m3</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">More information on the glass wool by St. Gobain ISOVER SA and their technical specifications can be found under http://www.isover.ch/</text>
        </generalComment>
        <tag> branded dataset without logo</tag>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="072976da-35f1-4afe-bad1-dbb458efcd1e">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2399:Manufacture of other non-metallic mineral products n.e.c.</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="131278d6-7d7e-11de-9ae2-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">CH</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Plant-specific data from Saint-Gobian ISOVER SA, CH-1522 Lucens.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <imageUrl index="0">https://db3.ecoinvent.org/images/2cbb45df-53df-4ba0-97bd-04777f7596ef</imageUrl>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Glasswool is made from natural sand to which recycled glass (cullet) and fluxing agents are added. The material is melted to 1100°C in an electric furnace. The fibre is formed by centrifugation through drilled disks. Fiberising is integral. Binding products as well as elements specific to the usage are added and the wool mat is polymerised and rolled. The product is then packaged.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2018-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
